  <prompt>
    Implement AttachmentClassificationJobHandler: download attachment from SPE, extract text
    via TextExtractorService, call IInvoiceAnalysisService.ClassifyAttachmentAsync, write
    classification + confidence + hints to sprk_document, set reviewstatus=ToReview for
    candidates/unknowns. Handle text extraction failures (classify as Unknown, confidence=0).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in background job processing and the job contract pattern.
    Follow ADR-004 for job patterns, ADR-015 for data governance, ADR-016 for bounded concurrency.
  </role>

  <goal>
    AttachmentClassificationJobHandler created following the EmailToDocumentJobHandler pattern.
    Handler downloads attachment, extracts text, classifies via AI, writes results to Dataverse.
    Text extraction failures handled gracefully (Unknown, confidence=0).
    Never creates Invoice or BillingEvent records — classification only.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      This handler is the first step in the finance intelligence pipeline. When an email attachment
      is created in SPE, this job classifies it as Invoice/NotInvoice/Unknown using AI. The handler
      downloads the file from SPE, extracts text, calls the InvoiceAnalysisService for classification,
      then writes the results back to the sprk_document record. Documents classified as candidates
      or unknowns get reviewstatus=ToReview so they appear in the review queue.

      The handler MUST be idempotent — safe under message replays. It must NOT create Invoice or
      BillingEvent records; those are created only after human review confirmation.
    </background>
